  "body": "- [ ] I've [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nI know the Event System is flagged \"experimental\" but as I understand the documentation, experiments and feedback are welcome so here it comes: I have a use case where I need `truffle compile` to make minor adjustments to some files in `/contracts` before running the actual compilation. I cannot get `compile:start` handler to fire, though.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nIn my `truffle-config.js`, I added the `subscribers` key:\r\n```javascript\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n    [...]\r\n    subscribers: {\r\n        testnetOverride: require('./testnet-override.js'),\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn the project root, I added `testnet-override.js`:\r\n```javascript\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n    handlers: {\r\n        \"compile:start\": [\r\n            function () {\r\n                console.log('foobar');\r\n            }\r\n        ],\r\n    },\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nI expect to see the `foobar` log output before the contracts are compiled.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nI get the regular compilation output with no errors but also no log output.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: MacOS 12.1\r\n* Ethereum client: truffle develop\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): v5.4.30\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v16.13.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): v8.1.0\r\n",
